Eight Pieces Of Art Stolen From Church Charity Exhibit
 May 23, 2007

Valuable art is missing from an Upper East Side church exhibit intended to help the homeless.

Officials with the Jan Hus Presbyterian Church say eight pieces worth more than $3,000 were stolen from the show meant to benefit the church's homeless outreach program.

The show was forced to cancel more than a week early Wednesday.

"It was really sad that someone would steal artwork from a church that is putting together an exhibition to empower homeless people,? said one parishioner.

The church may experience a financial loss, as it may have to pay the artists whose work is missing.

Police are investigating the incident.

